ZH: 他的决定是盲目的，没有经过深思熟虑。
EN: His decision was blind, without careful consideration.

ZH: 不要盲目地相信他的话。
EN: Don't blindly trust his words.

ZH: 盲目追求金钱只能带来痛苦。
EN: Blindly pursuing money can only bring pain.

ZH: 盲目追赶时尚并不重要。
EN: Blindly chasing after fashion is not important.

ZH: 盲目的怀疑只会伤害人与人之间的关系。
EN: Blind suspicion only hurts relationships between people.

ZH: 盲目地听从别人的指示并不明智。
EN: It's not wise to blindly follow other people's instructions.

ZH: 盲目的乐观有时会导致失望。
EN: Blind optimism can sometimes lead to disappointment.

ZH: 盲目争论只会加深隔阂。
EN: Blind arguing will only deepen the estrangement.

ZH: 盲目地批评别人只会带来负面影响。
EN: Blindly criticizing others will only bring negative consequences.

ZH: 他的判断力不足，常常做出盲目的决定。
EN: His judgment is lacking, often making blind decisions.

ZH: 不要因为一时的兴奋而盲目行动。
EN: Don't act blindly because of temporary excitement.

ZH: 盲目地追逐名利只会迷失自我。
EN: Blindly chasing fame and fortune will only lose oneself.

ZH: 不要为了追求自由而盲目反抗。
EN: Don't blindly resist for the sake of seeking freedom.

ZH: 盲目的恐惧只会束缚自己的能力。
EN: Blind fear will only restrain one's abilities.

ZH: 盲目追求权力会令人迷失方向。
EN: Blindly pursuing power can make one lose their direction.

ZH: 盲目的崇拜只会破坏平衡。
EN: Blind worship will only disrupt the balance.

ZH: 盲目地妄自菲薄不利于个人发展。
EN: Blindly belittling oneself is not conducive to personal development.

ZH: 盲目地从众只是一种逃避责任的方式。
EN: Blindly following the crowd is just a way to avoid responsibility.

ZH: 盲目自大只会给自己带来麻烦。
EN: Blind arrogance will only bring trouble upon oneself.

ZH: 盲目遵从规则有时会限制创造力。
EN: Blindly obeying rules can sometimes limit creativity.
